  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThere are a few strategies that can be employed that will harden our routing table from Sybil and Eclipse attacks. Some examples are listed here: https://github.com/ethereum/devp2p/blob/master/discv5/discv5-rationale.md#sybil-and-eclipse-attacks\r\n\r\nSpecifically we should implement:\r\n- Limiting the buckets to 2 nodes per /24 subnet\r\n- Limiting the entire table to 10 nodes per /24 subnet\r\n- Performing liveness checks on connected nodes and using this a age measure when deciding which nodes to keep in the table",
